t 1155","1155":"1155","Bef 1190":"before 1190","Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England":"Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Kentchurch, Herefordshire, England":"Kentchurch, Herefordshire, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Scudamore","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Skidmore  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Skidmore","meanings":["English (Staffordshire): of Norman origin, a variant of <b>Scudamore</b>, which most probably arises from a Norman French nickname for a knight who used a particular type of leather shield, from the unrecorded Norman French phrase, <i>escu de more</i> ‘Moor's shield’, a reference to a type of Moorish leather shield called an <i>adarga</i>, which was in widespread use not only in medieval Iberia and north Africa but also in Brittany.","History: The manor of Upton Scudamore in Wiltshire was held by Peter de Skydemore in 1216. The same manor was held by Godfrey Escudamore shortly after 1150. The Scudamore family claim descent from Ralph, recorded in Domesday Book (1086) as holder of <i>Opeton</i> (Upton), whose son was known as Reginald <i>Escudemor</i>."]}]},{"name":"Godfrey","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Old French name <i>Godefroy</i>, which is of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>god</i> ‘god’ (or <i>gōd</i> ‘good’) + <i>fred</i>, <i>frid</i> ‘peace’. This was adopted by the Normans, and brought to England by immigrants from the Low Countries and France. It was borne by a Norman saint (  <i>c.</i>1066–1115 ) who became bishop of Amiens. There has been considerable confusion with   Geoffrey ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Godfrey de Scudamore was born about 1128, in Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Reginald Scudamore, was 54 and his mother, Mauduit, was 42. He had at least 2 daughters with Matilda Bolbec. He died before 1190, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1128–Bef 1190":"umbes 1128–enne 1190","1088–Male":"1088–Surnud","1090–Male":"1090–Surnud","1095–1204":"1095–1204","1128–1190":"1128–1190","1136–Female":"1136–Surnud","1135–1203":"1135–1203","1155–1204":"1155–1204","1148–1191":"1148–1191","1075–1148":"1075–1148","1087–Female":"1087–Surnud","1190":"1190","1090":"1090","before 1148":"enne 1148","Abt 1128":"umbes 1128","1088":"1088","1087":"1087","1075":"1075","1095":"1095","1191":"1191","1128":"1128","13 June 1135":"13. juuni 1135","1204":"1204","1148":"1148","1203":"1203","1136":"1136","1135":"1135","Abt 1155":"umbes 1155","1155":"1155","Bef 1190":"enne 1190","Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, England":"Upton Scudamore, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kentchurch, Herefordshire, England":"Kentchurch, Herefordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1128–Bef 1190":"noin 1128–ennen vuotta 1190","1088–Male":"1088–Kuollut","1090–Male":"1090–Kuollut","1095–1204":"1095–1204","1128–1190":"1128–1190","1136–Female":"1136–Kuollut","1135–1203":"1135–1203","1155–1204":"1